"It must, however, be ramified enough to avoid long waiting lines at the distribution points. & Local standards Local standards should be respected. For example, installing a home watersupply system in a refugee camp is unwise if neighboring populations have to walk three kilometers to fetch water from a well. # & Cost\nTransporting water by tank trucks may be acceptable at the very beginning of an emergency, but the cost of such a measure should lead relief organizers to seek an alternative solution quickly. The ''ideal'' solution should take account of all these factors."